# Portfolio Project Rules

## Stack
Next.js 15 App Router, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind v4, static export to GitHub Pages.

## Must follow
- Use `assetPath()` from `@/lib/utils` for all public file URLs (resume, images).
- Edit content in `data/portfolio.ts`, not hardcoded in components.
- Never use `next start` — use `npm run start` (serves `out/`).
- Never add API routes or server-only Next.js features (`output: "export"`).
- Ignore legacy `src/` directory — active code is in `app/`, `components/`, `data/`.
- Deploy with `npm run deploy` (uses `build:pages` with `/portfolio` basePath and `--nojekyll` for `_next/` assets).

## Conventions
- `"use client"` only when hooks/events/browser APIs are needed.
- Use `cn()` for conditional Tailwind classes.
- Use `FadeIn` + `SectionHeading` for new sections.
- Keep styling in Tailwind utilities; theme tokens in `app/globals.css`.

## Scripts
- `npm run dev` — development
- `npm run build` — local production preview
- `npm run deploy` — GitHub Pages publish
